# Hypothesis Report

## Hypothesis ID
003-fdf946

## Branch
appworld-claude-sonnet-4.6-hyp-003-fdf946

## Hypothesis Statement
The agent fails Venmo tasks (2a163ab_*) because it doesn't know how to get relationships (roommates, siblings, coworkers) from contacts or the Venmo API workflow. Adding explicit guidance about supervisor contacts API and Venmo transaction APIs with exact signatures will enable the agent to correctly identify and like transactions involving specific relationships.

## Changes Made

| File | Action | Summary |
|------|--------|---------|
| src/agent.py | Modified | Added "Venmo Tasks" section to system prompt with exact API signatures for show_contacts, venmo.login, show_social_feed, and add_transaction_like |

## Metrics

| Metric | Value |
...

The +10pp accuracy gain (20% → 30%) comes from 82e2fac_3 passing, which is model variance (this task was also passing in the rolled-back 002 hypothesis).

## Recommendation

The hypothesis targeted Venmo tasks but did not fix them. All three Venmo tasks (2a163ab_1, 2a163ab_2, 2a163ab_3) remain at 1/6 tests passing, identical to the previous accepted state. The accuracy improvement from 20% to 30% is due to 82e2fac_3 passing, which is unrelated to the Venmo guidance and represents model variance.

Since the targeted failure class was not fixed, this change should be rolled back. The next iteration should investigate the actual API responses to understand why the Venmo workflow isn't working — the API signatures may be incorrect or there may be a mismatch between contact data and Venmo user identification.

**Decision: ROLLBACK**

